name: Hisuian Voltorb
flavorText: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Choose up to 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to that Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Kricketune
flavorText: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.
Ability1Text: Your Grass Pokémon in play, except any Kricketune, get +40 HP. You can't apply more than 1 Swelling Tune Ability at a time.

name: Magmortar
flavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack2Text: If Electivire is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Oricorio
flavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.
Ability1Text: All of your Fusion Strike Pokémon take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Lesson in Zeal Ability at a time.
Attack1Text: Put 5 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Lapras
flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Manaphy
flavorText: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Electivire
flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.
Attack1Text: If any of your Benched Magmortar have any damage counters on them, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Toxtricity
flavorText: It has an electrical organ on its chest. While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.
Ability1Text: If all your Pokémon in play are Fusion Strike Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon VMAX in play get -30 HP.

name: Mew
flavorText: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Lunatone
flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Deoxys
flavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has any Fusion Strike Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Diancie
flavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to your Benched Basic Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Comfey
flavorText: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card in the Lost Zone.

name: Solrock
flavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Lunatone.

name: Absol
flavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Thievul
flavorText: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has 2 or fewer Prize cards remaining, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to your Benched Pokémon V.

name: Magnezone
flavorText: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Altaria
flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, shuffle your deck, then put that card on top of it.

name: Latias
flavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Latios.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Pokémon VMAX.

name: Hisuian Goodra
flavorText: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy— it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to each of your Basic Pokémon that has any Metal Energy attached by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V.

name: Ditto
flavorText: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of any Basic Pokémon in your discard pile, except for Pokémon with a Rule Box (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

name: Dunsparce
flavorText: When it sees a person, it digs a hole with its tail to make its escape. If you happen to find one, consider yourself lucky.
Ability1Text: Colorless Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Weakness.

name: Miltank
flavorText: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it's been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Bibarel
flavorText: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

name: Swablu
flavorText: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Duskull
flavorText: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it's said.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

name: Paras
flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Mareep
flavorText: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You'll want to pet it because it's cute, but if you use your bare hand, you'll get a painful shock.

name: Leafeon VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Entei V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Simisear VSTAR
Attack1Text: You may discard up to 5 cards from the top of your deck. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy card in your discard pile. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Suicune V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Lumineon V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.

name: Glaceon VSTAR
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Raikou V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Zeraora VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon in play that has an Ability.

name: Zeraora VSTAR
Attack1Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon 4 times. (You can choose the same Pokémon more than once.) For each time you chose a Pokémon, do 60 damage to it. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Mewtwo VSTAR
Attack1Text: Discard up to 3 Psychic Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 90 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 120 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon V. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Deoxys VMAX
Ability1Text: All of your Pokémon take 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon VSTAR (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Deoxys VSTAR
Attack1Text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon V. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Hatterene VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may move up to 2 damage counters from your Pokémon to your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Zacian V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Drapion V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Single Strike, Rapid Strike, and Fusion Strike Pokémon in play.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Darkrai VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may put up to 2 Item cards from your discard pile into your hand. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Hisuian Samurott V
Attack1Text: Discard up to 2 Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Hisuian Samurott VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may put 4 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 110 more damage.

name: Hoopa V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in play, it is Psychic and Darkness type.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Zamazenta V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 5 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Regigigas VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, if your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. They discard that Pokémon and all attached cards. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Hisuian Zoroark VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 7 cards. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

name: Origin Forme Palkia VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may attach up to 3 Water Energy cards from your discard pile to your Water Pokémon in any way you like. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Origin Forme Dialga VSTAR
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Take another turn after this one. (Skip Pokémon Checkup.) (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Giratina VSTAR
Attack1Text: Put 2 Energy attached to your Pokémon in the Lost Zone.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if you have 10 or more cards in the Lost Zone. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Arceus VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon V in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
